00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:52,400
Thanks a lot.

258
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:03,700
Kneel down.

259
00:30:03,900 --> 00:30:05,500
- Like you're praying.
- She...

260
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:08,000
Do the down-facing dog.

261
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:09,500
Make it super-size.

262
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:14,000
She said we could get some fruit.

263
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:46,600
- You have to earn the food.
- How do you earn it?

264
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,200
Put in your time. Take one of those.

265
00:31:04,100 --> 00:31:08,200
WOMAN: I was so high, I didn't notice
my visa had run out.

266
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:11,300
I couldn't pay the fine to leave.

267
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:16,100
A bloke I met said he'd pay the fine
and give me some pocket money.

268
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:20,600
I just had to take some packets
and stuff them inside me.

269
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,900
You're telling that
smack-in-the-box tale again?

270
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,600
Yankee girl.

271
00:31:29,700 --> 00:31:33,100
- What's with her?
- She thinks you're fun to piss off.

272
00:31:33,500 --> 00:31:37,800
You're the new show
at the brokedown palace.

273
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:42,000
- When's checkout time?
- Check out anytime, man.

274
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:46,200
You find freedom here
and in here...

275
00:31:46,900 --> 00:31:48,300
...and in here.

276
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:40,800
- What's with her?
- She thought she'd get pardoned.

277
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:45,000
Everybody thinks they'll get a pardon
from the crown. Makes me sick.

278
00:32:45,300 --> 00:32:49,500
Addicted to fantasy. That road
leads straight into the ground.

279
00:32:55,900 --> 00:32:59,300
It happened at least once.
The old mama-san...

280
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:02,300
...she was here one day
and gone the next.

281
00:33:02,700 --> 00:33:06,200
- The guards were in a proper lather too.
- What happened?

282
00:33:06,500 --> 00:33:08,000
Nobody knows.

283
00:33:08,300 --> 00:33:13,000
We think a certain guard opened
the gate, and she just walks away.

284
00:33:14,300 --> 00:33:16,200
Which guard was it?

285
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:19,400
Velie. We think Velie.

286
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:25,600
So someone bribed Velie? With what?

287
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:29,300
I heard it was $ 100 for the gate
and a car waiting.

288
00:33:29,700 --> 00:33:32,400
Please. If they catch you escaping...

289
00:33:32,700 --> 00:33:35,200
...they add 15 years to your sentence.

290
00:33:35,500 --> 00:33:38,500
Mama-san could have been shot
in the street.

291
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:41,400
All this talk is a waste of time.

292
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:44,800
You should get in touch
with Yankee Hank.

293
00:33:45,100 --> 00:33:47,400
- Who?
- Yankee Hank.

294
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:52,900
- He's a barrister. That's a stretch.
- Yankee Hank's a damn good lawyer.

295
00:33:55,100 --> 00:33:58,200
If he's so good,
how come you never called him?

296
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:01,500
An impoverished soul like myself?

297
00:34:01,800 --> 00:34:04,200
He like American folding money.

298
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:05,800
You're not lying.

299
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:10,500
Of course, if I had the dosh,
I'd try Velie first.

300
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,700
Dad!

301
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:49,700
I'm so sorry.

302
00:34:50,100 --> 00:34:51,300
What?

303
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:53,900
I'm sorry I lied about Hawaii.

304
00:34:54,200 --> 00:34:55,900
Honey, it's all right.

305
00:34:56,200 --> 00:35:00,900
We're gonna get you out of here.
Don't worry. Whatever it takes.

306
00:35:01,300 --> 00:35:03,100
Tell everyone I didn't do it.

307
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:08,000
- What?
- We didn't do it!

308
00:35:08,300 --> 00:35:11,400
They know that. Everybody
knows that, baby.

309
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:14,600
Everybody back home
misses you, sweetie.

310
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:19,500
- Why would you want to come here?
- I'm so sorry.

311
00:35:19,900 --> 00:35:22,800
That's all right.
We'll find a way, okay?

312
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:26,200
Everything is gonna work out,
I promise.

313
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:28,200
It'll be okay.

314
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:31,800
I love you.

315
00:35:43,900 --> 00:35:46,200
He's going to get us out.

316
00:35:46,500 --> 00:35:50,000
- He said us?
- Yeah, he wants to see you.

317
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
You always thought
you were so smart.

318
00:36:03,500 --> 00:36:05,800
I hope you're proud of yourself.

319
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,400
- Mr. Davis...
- You're a schemer.

320
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:13,000
You think I don't know you?
You are dead wrong.

321
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:16,700
Every word out of your mouth is a lie.

322
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:21,500
Six years old, paint on your hands,
on our couch.

323
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:23,500
"I didn't do it."

324
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:28,500
16 years old, the beer cans
in my car. "I didn't do it."

325
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:31,800
Let me hear you say it again.

326
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:34,300
Say it in here.

327
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:37,000
Come on, for old times' sake.

328
00:36:39,100 --> 00:36:41,900
I didn't do it!

329
00:36:48,100 --> 00:36:50,100
I'm so glad he's here.

330
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,900
He's being so great about it.

331
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:56,200
He really knows
how to grease the wheels.

332
00:36:56,600 --> 00:36:58,900
He'll know what to do.

333
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:01,300
- What's the matter?
- Nothing.

334
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:03,900
- Why aren't you excited?
- I am.

335
00:37:04,300 --> 00:37:06,900
Did he tell you
he spoke to your dad?

336
00:37:07,500 --> 00:37:09,000
Goddamn it!

337
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:10,200
You like?

338
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:11,800
Good fish heads.

339
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:16,300
No! It's a matter of days now.

340
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:50,900
DARLENE:
I told the detective the truth.

341
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:56,700
I told him about Nick Parks and all
the events leading up to our arrest.

342
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:01,400
I signed a statement...

343
00:38:01,700 --> 00:38:05,400
...assuming it was just a translation
of what I said.

344
00:38:05,900 --> 00:38:10,300
But these aren't my words.
I never said any of that.

345
00:38:10,700 --> 00:38:13,300
That's the truth.

346
00:38:29,700 --> 00:38:31,500
[SPEAKS IN THAl]

347
00:38:40,100 --> 00:38:43,100
- What happened?
- Don't worry, we'll appeal.

348
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:47,400
You can request a pardon.
He found you both guilty.

349
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:50,500
- For how long?
- Good news. It wasn't life.

350
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:53,100
You both got numbered sentences.

351
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:56,600
- For how long?
- 33 years.

352
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,700
- Daddy!
- Honey, I'll take care of everything.

353
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:07,600
Yes, we're all over it.

354
00:39:07,900 --> 00:39:09,900
Listen, I gotta go.

355
00:39:10,900 --> 00:39:13,500
Sorry about that. Couldn't be helped.

356
00:39:13,900 --> 00:39:17,200
- I know how you must feel.
- Fellas, look...

357
00:39:17,600 --> 00:39:20,400
I know what goes on around here.

358
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,900
They take drugs seriously.

359
00:39:23,300 --> 00:39:25,600
- There's no doubt...
- Come on.

360
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:30,400
Nobody here really wants
to stop the drugs. They're all...

361
00:39:33,400 --> 00:39:38,400
I don't care if Thailand drowns
in heroin. That's their business.

362
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:42,400
Your business is to help
American citizens.

363
00:39:43,700 --> 00:39:46,100
She didn't do anything.

364
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:50,200
They're not gonna make
an example of my little girl...

365
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:52,600
...with some trumped-up charge.

366
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:55,200
You pull strings all the time.

367
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:59,200
You could pull them for my daughter.

368
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:04,500
The DEA will continue
our investigation.

369
00:40:04,900 --> 00:40:09,700
If we find the alleged man
who lured your daughter into this...

370
00:40:10,100 --> 00:40:13,300
...we'll certainly
introduce that in an appeal.

371
00:40:15,700 --> 00:40:18,400
I know this is difficult for you.

372
00:40:18,700 --> 00:40:22,300
But the best thing
you can do is go home.

373
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,800
Go back to your family.

374
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:30,700
Nothing will fall through the cracks.
We'll keep you informed.

375
00:40:31,200 --> 00:40:33,200
That's a promise.

376
00:40:36,900 --> 00:40:38,500
ALICE:
So here we are.

377
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:41,600
Just two more drug smugglers.

378
00:40:42,300 --> 00:40:45,600
I don 't even know why
I'm making this tape.

379
00:41:07,900 --> 00:41:09,500
How do you do?

380
00:41:09,900 --> 00:41:11,400
I'm Henry Greene.

381
00:41:12,300 --> 00:41:14,100
Hank Greene, actually.

382
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:16,400
- Who are you?
- Yankee Hank?

383
00:41:16,700 --> 00:41:21,300
Yankee Hank, or Hank the Yank,
or whatever.

384
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:26,000
What can I do for you?
You want a cigarette?

385
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:30,500
- So you're like a lawyer?
- No, I am a lawyer.

386
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:34,800
Is this pro bono work that you do?

387
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:38,100
Pro bono? No.

388
00:41:38,700 --> 00:41:41,700
So I listened to your narrative.

389
00:41:43,900 --> 00:41:47,700
Forgive me if I'm blunt,
but there's nothing there.

390
00:41:48,100 --> 00:41:52,800
You just claim you didn't know
about the smack. If you're lying...

391
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:57,500
...you're brainy and stupid.
If it's true, you're just stupid.

392
00:41:57,900 --> 00:42:00,600
So I gotta ask a few questions.

393
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:05,000
Who was carrying
the luggage with the drugs?

394
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,000
I was.

395
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:12,900
You had a couple kilos of heroin.
You didn't notice the extra weight?

396
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:16,600
- I didn't. I just didn't.
- We were late.

397
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:18,400
Yeah, of course.

398
00:42:18,900 --> 00:42:21,600
- Who packed the bag?
- I did.

399
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:28,200
Alice, what does your father do?

400
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,200
Works at Bekins.

401
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:34,100
- Does he run a branch office?
- He rents trucks.

402
00:42:35,200 --> 00:42:36,900
And your mom?

403
00:42:37,700 --> 00:42:40,000
She died when I was 7.

404
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:42,900
Sorry to hear that.
What happened?

405
00:42:43,300 --> 00:42:45,000
Car accident.

406
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:48,700
- And your dad?
- Insurance.

407
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:52,700
And my mom sells real estate.
Part-time.

408
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:57,700
I'll call to see
if they'll contribute...

409
00:42:58,100 --> 00:43:00,700
...to their daughters' liberation
fund.

410
00:43:01,100 --> 00:43:03,900
- What are you gonna do?
- Get you out.

411
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:07,500
Start writing letters
to lawmakers back home.

412
00:43:08,500 --> 00:43:12,100
Congressmen. The president.
If you know a priest.

413
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:15,300
You want me to write
to my congressman?

414
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:18,500
That's right. I'll be in touch, girls.

415
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:25,700
- He's totally sleazy.
- Don't say that.

416
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,700
Greene? You say you're Thai?

417
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,700
HANK:
Well, I might as well be.

418
00:43:31,100 --> 00:43:34,300
I'm American, but I know
their justice system.

419
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:37,500
- Now there's an oxymoron.
- Yeah.

420
00:43:38,600 --> 00:43:42,600
My wife, Yon,
is also a practicing attorney...

421
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:44,500
...born in Bangkok.

422
00:43:44,800 --> 00:43:49,600
We've helped a lot of families.
We could help your daughter.

423
00:43:50,200 --> 00:43:52,100
What do you want out of this?

424
00:43:52,700 --> 00:43:54,900
I'm just a broker.

425
00:43:56,600 --> 00:43:59,100
We're looking for our usual retainer.

426
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:01,700
Which is...

427
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:03,500
...$ 15,000.

428
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:05,600
$ 15,000?

429
00:44:07,000 --> 00:44:11,200
7500 to try to get a hearing
and 7500 if we do.

430
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:14,500
That's for both girls.

431
00:44:15,100 --> 00:44:17,000
Wait, for both girls?

432
00:44:17,500 --> 00:44:21,900
- Darlene needs her own trial.
- You don't want to do that.

433
00:44:22,300 --> 00:44:26,700
The strongest point is
that Alice didn't sign a confession.

434
00:44:27,500 --> 00:44:32,600
Separate them, and you're begging
for Darlene to be singled out.

435
00:44:35,700 --> 00:44:38,700
Do you wanna take a day or two?

436
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:40,800
No. God, no.

437
00:44:42,100 --> 00:44:43,500
I'll get the money.

438
00:44:43,900 --> 00:44:46,800
I'll call Marano
and wire it to you.

439
00:44:47,200 --> 00:44:50,100
Great. We'll be in touch.

440
00:45:11,700 --> 00:45:13,800
Who got you these tickets?

441
00:45:14,100 --> 00:45:17,100
Same guy who introduced me
to these babies.

442
00:45:17,400 --> 00:45:20,200
Well, hello there. Thank you.

443
00:45:21,900 --> 00:45:24,000
Our next Minister of Justice.

444
00:45:24,400 --> 00:45:26,300
He's worked hard for it.

445
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:29,200
He's working his fingers to the bone.

446
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:36,000
I love that guy!
I love that guy, man!

447
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,500
This is great.

448
00:45:37,700 --> 00:45:39,700
No problem.

449
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:43,400
So when do I get the file
on Davis and Marano?

450
00:45:45,400 --> 00:45:49,200
Those girls have no chance
of getting out of there.

451
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,100
Who's Nick Parks?

452
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:52,700
Who?

453
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:55,800
Why couldn't you find him?

454
00:45:57,100 --> 00:45:59,900
The cops say the girls made him up.

455
00:46:00,200 --> 00:46:02,800
Even if he did plant the six kilos...

456
00:46:03,200 --> 00:46:05,900
...you know he'd never confess.

457
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:07,500
- Six?
- Yeah.

458
00:46:07,900 --> 00:46:10,200
The shit was in their backpacks.

459
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:15,900
As far as the Thais are concerned,
they're guilty. Guilty or not.

460
00:46:16,300 --> 00:46:18,300
Take a pass on this one.

461
00:46:20,200 --> 00:46:22,700
After you give me the file, Roy.

462
00:46:30,500 --> 00:46:33,800
Why not find out
who bought the plane tickets?

463
00:46:34,300 --> 00:46:38,600
You'd think that'd be the easiest way
to catch this guy.

464
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:41,000
If he exists.

465
00:46:42,300 --> 00:46:44,300
He sure doesn't exist in this.

466
00:46:44,700 --> 00:46:46,500
What do you believe?

467
00:46:47,700 --> 00:46:50,000
I believe that, either way...

468
00:46:50,300 --> 00:46:53,400
...we'll be able to afford a new car.

469
00:46:53,700 --> 00:46:55,900
This is Jagkrit's trophy photo.

470
00:46:56,800 --> 00:47:01,300
Look at that, they're so arrogant,
they don't try to finesse it.

471
00:47:01,700 --> 00:47:04,900
All that narcotic
in that little backpack.

472
00:47:06,300 --> 00:47:07,800
I don't think so.

473
00:47:13,300 --> 00:47:18,100
- That's great.
- It's just a hearing for a retrial.

474
00:47:18,600 --> 00:47:22,200
I also talked to
the lady who runs the hotel.

475
00:47:22,500 --> 00:47:26,800
Either she's not involved
or she's the best liar I've met.

476
00:47:27,200 --> 00:47:29,000
What about Nick?

477
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:32,100
Parks isn't the magic bullet.

478
00:47:32,400 --> 00:47:36,100
Even if we do find him,
it's your word against his.

479
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:38,800
But we're still looking.

480
00:47:40,700 --> 00:47:43,600
Darlene, I need a moment with Alice.

481
00:47:44,600 --> 00:47:46,000
Sure.

482
00:47:55,800 --> 00:47:58,900
Nick was staying at
the Queen Victoria?

483
00:48:00,300 --> 00:48:03,000
My wife found a maid there...

484
00:48:03,300 --> 00:48:08,200
...who said there was a young man
there who matched Parks' description.

485
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:10,300
So, good, right?

486
00:48:11,900 --> 00:48:14,400
The maid remembered him with a girl.

487
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:16,700
But when showed this picture...

488
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:21,300
...guess who the maid picked out
as the girl he was with.

489
00:48:23,600 --> 00:48:25,000
Me.

490
00:48:26,300 --> 00:48:28,900
Okay, I was at Nick's hotel.

491
00:48:29,300 --> 00:48:33,200
And he came on to me,
but I told him to forget it.

492
00:48:34,300 --> 00:48:37,700
He never even mentioned drugs.
I swear it.

493
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:41,900
- Is there anything else I should know?
- No.

494
00:48:44,700 --> 00:48:49,100
Do you have to tell Darlene?
That would be really weird.

495
00:48:50,800 --> 00:48:53,900
- I see no reason to tell anyone.
- Thank you.

496
00:48:55,300 --> 00:48:57,800
Now I have a favor to ask you.

497
00:48:58,100 --> 00:49:00,500
I haven't gotten your father's check.

498
00:49:02,200 --> 00:49:05,500
I need you to talk to him.

499
00:49:13,900 --> 00:49:15,500
[PHONE RINGS]

500
00:49:18,900 --> 00:49:21,300
Hi, hello. Hi.

501
00:49:24,300 --> 00:49:25,500
Alice?

502
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:28,400
My God...

503
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:30,200
Are you okay?

504
00:49:31,500 --> 00:49:33,400
Where are you? You sound close.

505
00:49:34,700 --> 00:49:37,100
I'm still here in Thailand.

506
00:49:39,400 --> 00:49:43,300
I'm trying to get there.
I would have been there sooner...

507
00:49:44,100 --> 00:49:48,300
It ain't about money,
but the doc says my diabetes...

508
00:49:49,900 --> 00:49:52,300
