this kind of people.

758
01:21:35,300 --> 01:21:39,300
The cops and customs guys
get paid extra money...

759
01:21:39,800 --> 01:21:42,300
...when they make a dope bust?

760
01:21:43,400 --> 01:21:45,800
So we were like a walking bribe.

761
01:21:47,100 --> 01:21:48,000
Yes.

762
01:21:48,200 --> 01:21:52,400
Now they'll add 15 more years
for trying to escape.

763
01:22:02,700 --> 01:22:05,600
You have been busy, Mr. Greene.

764
01:22:06,200 --> 01:22:09,800
- Please, sit down.
- Thank you.

765
01:22:10,100 --> 01:22:15,100
Getting those two girls set free
has earned you a few shekels?

766
01:22:15,900 --> 01:22:17,600
A few.

767
01:22:18,100 --> 01:22:22,100
I believe I'm really the source
of your good fortune.

768
01:22:23,400 --> 01:22:24,900
How's that, sir?

769
01:22:25,100 --> 01:22:28,500
I catch drug smugglers,
and you defend them.

770
01:22:28,900 --> 01:22:32,700
I feel I'm owed some sort of
tribute from you.

771
01:22:33,300 --> 01:22:35,900
It's a regular food chain.

772
01:22:36,200 --> 01:22:39,200
Yes, that's exactly what it is.

773
01:22:39,500 --> 01:22:43,500
I guess Skip Carn would know
a thing or two...

774
01:22:43,900 --> 01:22:46,400
...about paying tribute to you.

775
01:22:48,700 --> 01:22:51,300
I expect a little more from you.

776
01:22:51,600 --> 01:22:55,900
You're acting like...
What's that American expression?

777
01:22:56,300 --> 01:22:58,400
An ambulance chaser.

778
01:22:59,100 --> 01:23:04,100
I'm kind of a loose cannon.
Know that American expression?

779
01:23:04,600 --> 01:23:07,800
I'd love to blow this
out of the water.

780
01:23:08,100 --> 01:23:12,900
You have a cozy relationship
with a known drug trafficker.

781
01:23:13,300 --> 01:23:16,400
This is exactly the kind of thing...

782
01:23:16,800 --> 01:23:19,600
...Americans love watching on TV.

783
01:23:20,000 --> 01:23:24,800
Two American girls' lives ruined
by a sleazy smuggler...

784
01:23:25,200 --> 01:23:28,200
...and the greedy cop in his pocket.

785
01:23:28,700 --> 01:23:33,600
You'll have to get ready for
Larry King. You'll love him.

786
01:23:34,000 --> 01:23:38,200
Barbara Walters will probably
have pictures of you.

787
01:23:38,600 --> 01:23:42,800
Barbara and the parents
will go into the bedroom:

788
01:23:43,100 --> 01:23:47,600
"This is Darlene's room,
exactly as she left it."

789
01:23:48,000 --> 01:23:51,700
- Teddy bears...
- Is there a point to this fantasy?

790
01:23:52,100 --> 01:23:55,700
Yes, sir, it's a simple point.

791
01:23:56,500 --> 01:23:58,300
I need your help.

792
01:24:08,500 --> 01:24:10,500
That's a good accent.

793
01:24:10,800 --> 01:24:14,900
My Spanish teacher always told me,
"Good ear, bad memory."

794
01:24:16,300 --> 01:24:20,100
- How's Darlene doing?
- She's better.

795
01:24:21,800 --> 01:24:26,200
- We'll just wait for her.
- Can I ask you something?

796
01:24:26,700 --> 01:24:30,100
Since there's no money left,
why are you here?

797
01:24:31,100 --> 01:24:35,100
No matter how I look at it,
you don't deserve this.

798
01:24:37,300 --> 01:24:41,400
- Even if I did it?
- Yeah, but...

799
01:24:42,400 --> 01:24:45,800
You didn't do it.
We both know it.

800
01:24:59,500 --> 01:25:02,700
I wanted you to hear this
at the same time.

801
01:25:03,600 --> 01:25:05,600
You're gonna get to go home.

802
01:25:08,000 --> 01:25:11,900
- How?
- You'll have to sign a statement.

803
01:25:12,300 --> 01:25:15,000
Admit you're wrong. Forget Nick...

804
01:25:15,400 --> 01:25:18,200
- A statement?
- I can't do that.

805
01:25:18,600 --> 01:25:22,500
This is the official,
face-saving confession.

806
01:25:22,800 --> 01:25:26,600
You corroborate the police
version of events.

807
01:25:27,000 --> 01:25:29,400
That's our part of the deal.

808
01:25:30,800 --> 01:25:34,000
Then the crown will pardon you.

809
01:25:34,300 --> 01:25:36,100
Then you get to go home.

810
01:26:26,900 --> 01:26:28,300
All right.

811
01:26:29,500 --> 01:26:31,000
It's okay.

812
01:27:35,300 --> 01:27:38,100
No pardon: Narcotic offender.

813
01:27:38,500 --> 01:27:41,500
- What's the problem?
- No pardon.

814
01:27:41,800 --> 01:27:45,100
Your Minister of Justice has agreed.

815
01:27:45,500 --> 01:27:48,900
You tell him that we have
an agreement.

816
01:27:49,200 --> 01:27:53,800
I'm sorry.
They are narcotics smugglers.

817
01:27:54,200 --> 01:27:57,100
You son of a bitch, we have a deal.

818
01:27:57,500 --> 01:28:01,300
Yes, nicely done.
You really had me going.

819
01:28:01,600 --> 01:28:04,800
But now there is no more Skip Carn.

820
01:28:05,200 --> 01:28:08,100
No one will get to him, so no deal.

821
01:28:13,200 --> 01:28:14,400
Wait.

822
01:28:18,500 --> 01:28:20,400
No, get them off me.

823
01:28:49,200 --> 01:28:51,300
You may speak English.

824
01:28:52,800 --> 01:28:57,300
My best friend is not a drug smuggler.
She is innocent.

825
01:28:58,200 --> 01:28:59,700
She's innocent.

826
01:28:59,900 --> 01:29:02,900
All she ever did wrong
was to trust me.

827
01:29:05,600 --> 01:29:10,100
Here you believe one friend
knows what the other does.

828
01:29:10,500 --> 01:29:12,200
Maybe that's friendship...

829
01:29:12,500 --> 01:29:16,800
...but I'm American, and I was not
that kind of a friend.

830
01:29:17,100 --> 01:29:19,000
I know this.

831
01:29:21,300 --> 01:29:24,700
Because I did it.
Because I was foolish...

832
01:29:26,400 --> 01:29:30,400
...and jealous.
I was afraid she'd drift away.

833
01:29:30,800 --> 01:29:33,800
I was afraid I was gonna lose her.

834
01:29:35,400 --> 01:29:37,900
She never knew. It was all me.

835
01:29:38,200 --> 01:29:42,500
She spent all this time
in your prison for my mistakes.

836
01:29:43,900 --> 01:29:45,700
I'm sorry.

837
01:29:47,100 --> 01:29:51,300
Please, if you need someone
to do the time, I'll do it.

838
01:29:51,700 --> 01:29:55,900
I'll do her time and mine.
Just let her go, please.

839
01:30:07,600 --> 01:30:12,500
Then you're of strong character
and would lie to save your friend?

840
01:30:13,800 --> 01:30:16,600
No, I am of weak character.

841
01:30:17,000 --> 01:30:20,300
And I just want to
make up for my mistakes.

842
01:30:20,800 --> 01:30:23,900
If you're lying to
save your friend...

843
01:30:24,500 --> 01:30:28,600
...then you're of sufficient character
to earn what you want.

844
01:30:29,800 --> 01:30:32,200
If you're telling the truth...

845
01:30:32,500 --> 01:30:36,800
...then your friend is innocent
and should go free.

846
01:30:37,200 --> 01:30:41,300
If you are willing to serve
her term and yours...

847
01:30:41,800 --> 01:30:44,100
...your friend is pardoned.

848
01:30:50,100 --> 01:30:52,500
Thank you. Thank you.

849
01:31:27,300 --> 01:31:29,800
Darlene must go soon.

850
01:31:47,600 --> 01:31:49,800
You're a very good liar.

851
01:31:51,100 --> 01:31:52,900
You didn't do it.

852
01:31:54,200 --> 01:31:56,300
I know you didn't do it.

853
01:31:57,600 --> 01:31:59,600
I don't think I can leave you.

854
01:32:03,300 --> 01:32:05,700
If I say it was the truth...

855
01:32:06,200 --> 01:32:09,700
...you'll hate me.
And if I say I lied...

856
01:32:10,000 --> 01:32:15,100
...then when you go home,
all the time with your family...

857
01:32:15,600 --> 01:32:18,400
You won't be able to just be happy.

858
01:32:20,200 --> 01:32:24,000
So let's just say it was
the right thing to do.

859
01:32:29,000 --> 01:32:31,300
Let's just leave it at that.

860
01:32:42,500 --> 01:32:43,700
Come, Darlene.

861
01:32:55,000 --> 01:32:58,400
- I'm going to get you out of here.
- I know.

862
01:33:02,300 --> 01:33:06,100
Go, Dar. I need you to.

863
01:33:07,700 --> 01:33:09,300
Please.

864
01:34:44,600 --> 01:34:49,100
ALICE: A lot of people won 't
understand why I said I did it.

865
01:34:49,500 --> 01:34:52,500
But for me, it was
the right thing to do.

866
01:34:53,400 --> 01:34:56,800
Maybe more right than
anything I ever did.

867
01:34:58,400 --> 01:35:01,600
Darlene and Hank won 't stop trying...

868
01:35:02,700 --> 01:35:04,600
...till I'm out of here.

869
01:35:06,000 --> 01:35:07,600
Until I'm free.

